tossup_question: -   –  For a given reaction, the rate constant is equal to 93 liters squared per moles squared per second. What is the order of this reaction?
bonus_question: -   –  A closed vessel contains nitrogen gas, oxygen gas, and nitrogen dioxide gas. Nitrogen dioxide has a positive enthalpy of formation. Identify all of the following three changes that would shift the equilibrium to the products: 1) Increasing the temperature; 2) Increasing the pressure by adding nitrogen dioxide gas; 3) Increasing the pressure by adding an inert gas.
